    "Background": {
      "text": "Baclofen\n(Lioresal) is an anti-spasmodic that works on the as a GABA-B agonist\nPrimarily used in patients with\nmultiple sclerosis\n,\ncerebral palsy\n, and spinal cord injuries\nOften administered intrathecally but does have an oral formulation\nWithdrawal symptoms thought to be caused by decreased GABA activation",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Baclofen",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Baclofen"
        },
